t gi thuyt v i thit Gi thit : H0= tc tng trng ca cc lnh vc xy dng v dch v l ging nhau i thit : H1 = tc tng trng ca cc lnh vc xy dng v dch v l khc nhau

# To d liu gi nh
xay_dung <- df[10, 2:ncol(df)]
dich_vu <- df[11, 2:ncol(df)]

# Thc hin kim nh t-test
result <- t.test(xay_dung, dich_vu)

# In kt qu
print(result)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  xay_dung and dich_vu
## t = -12.447, df = 35.919, p-value = 1.369e-14
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -698991.9 -503111.8
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##  99795.17 700847.06

Kt qu kim tra t Welch Two Sample cho thy s khc bit c ngha thng k gia cc phng tin ca cc nhm xay_dung (Xy dng) v dich_vu (Dch v). Di y l mt s im chnh t u ra:

1. t-statistic: Gi tr t l -12.447, cho thy s khc bit ng k gia gi tr trung bnh ca hai nhm.

2. t do (df): Mc t do xp x 35.919.

3. p-value: Gi tr p cc k thp (1.369e-14), nh hn nhiu so vi mc ngha in hnh (v d: 0.05). iu ny cho thy bng chng mnh m bc b gi thuyt H0 chp nhn i thuyt H1.

4. Khong tin cy : Khong tin cy 95% cho s khc bit v phng tin l (-698991.9, -503111.8). Khong thi gian ny khng cha s khng, h tr thm bng chng v s khc bit ng k.

5. c tnh mu: Gi tr trung bnh ca xay_dung l 99795.17 v gi tr trung bnh ca dich_vu l 700847.06.

Kt thc: Gi tr p l cc k nh, cho thy bng chng mnh m bc b gi thuyt tc tng trng ca cc lnh vc xy dng v dch v l ging nhau. Do , da trn th nghim ny, chng ta c th kt lun rng c s khc bit c ngha thng k v tc tng trng gia cc lnh vc Xy dng v Dch v(Chp nhn i thuyt ). da trn gi tr trung bnh v khong tin cy cho thy ngnh xy dng c tc tng trng thp hn ngnh dch v

for (col in colnames(df)) {
  # To dataframe mi t ct hin ti
  data <- data.frame(
    group = df$X,
    value = df[, col]
  )

  # V biu  ct v n nhn trn trc x
  print(ggplot(data, aes(x = group, y = value, fill = group)) +
    geom_col(width = 1, color = "white") +
    theme_minimal() +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
    ggtitle(paste("Distribution of", col)))
}
